<br>
Aside from uber drops, the best of the &quot;fairly&quot; commonly available ones is the Tranquil (T-) Staff. 29/30 with an awesome proc called &quot;One Hundred Blows&quot; (which doesn't work til lvl 50? or so) but a huge wt of 10.0. This weapon outdamages most 1 hand combos, but is very expensive. Another expensive one is the Amygdalan War Staff, 37/36 with +8 Dex, +8 Sta, +75 Hp, wt 5.0. Other common staffs that monks use are Peacebringer 28/30 with wt of 10.0 and Imbued Fighter's Staff 38/40, wt 4.0. They are also somewhat expensive and run several thousand plat.<br>
<br>
Personally I just stuck with 1hand weapons and used a lame Bamboo Bo Stick 8/20 to keep my 2H Blunt skill caught up until I could afford a good weapon. Then I switched to a fairly cheap Wu's Quivering Staff 23/28 for a while. I've been using a Peacebringer for the last few levels, but I'm saving up for the T-Staff.<br>
<br>
I don't know of any half-decent no drop staffs, other than &quot;uber&quot; loot from boss mobs.  <p>Royceli, Lvl 57 Human Monk <BR>
